---
description: Prevent Cursor from being credited on git commits
alwaysApply: true
---

Never add "Co-authored-by: Cursor", "Made-with: Cursor", cursoragent@cursor.com, or any Cursor attribution to commit messages or PR descriptions.

When committing, use plain messages only (e.g. git commit -m "message"). If attribution was added, amend the commit to remove it before pushing.
